# Desktop App UI Standards

Follow these practices when building or updating the NOVA manager app.

## Typography

- **Body text**: 14–16px ( Tailwind: `text-sm`–`text-base`)
- **Labels / secondary**: 12–14px (`text-xs`–`text-sm`)
- **Section headings**: 16–18px (`text-base`–`text-lg`)
- **Page titles**: 20–24px (`text-xl`–`text-2xl`)
- **Currency / key data**: 14–16px; use `text-base` for important totals
- **Minimum size**: Avoid below 12px (`text-xs`)

## Spacing & Density

- **Card padding**: 16–24px (`p-4`–`p-6`)
- **Gaps**: 8–16px (`gap-2`–`gap-4`) between related items; 24–32px between sections
- **Line height**: Use default 1.5 or `leading-relaxed` for body text
- **Touch targets**: Min 44px height for interactive elements

## Layout

- **Max content width**: ~1440px (`max-w-7xl` or similar)
- **Grid alignment**: Use 8px base unit; Tailwind spacing handles this
- **Columns**: Prefer 2–3 columns on desktop for scannable data

## Responsive

- Use `sm:` and `lg:` breakpoints for desktop enhancements (e.g. larger fonts, more padding)
- Keep mobile-first; add desktop styles from `sm:` up
- Quick totals / data cards: compact on mobile; `sm:text-base`, `sm:text-sm` for labels on desktop

## Interaction

- **Hover states**: On buttons and links
- **Focus**: Visible focus rings (`focus-visible:ring-2`)
- **Click targets**: Min ~32px; prefer 40–44px for buttons/icons
